#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.geometric.rst:4
msgid "numpy.random.Generator.geometric"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.geometric.rst:8
msgid "method"
msgstr "方法"

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:2
msgid "Draw samples from the geometric distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:4
msgid ""
"Bernoulli trials are experiments with one of two outcomes: success or "
"failure (an example of such an experiment is flipping a coin).  The "
"geometric distribution models the number of trials that must be run in order "
"to achieve success.  It is therefore supported on the positive integers, ``k "
"= 1, 2, ...``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:10
msgid "The probability mass function of the geometric distribution is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:12
msgid ""
"f(k) = (1 - p)^{k - 1} p\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:14
msgid "where `p` is the probability of success of an individual trial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr "參數"

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:19
msgid "**p**"
msgstr "**p**"

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:-1
msgid "float or array_like of floats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:19
msgid "The probability of success of an individual trial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:25
msgid "**size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:-1
msgid "int or tuple of ints, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.geometric:22
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n * "
"k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default), a single value is "
"returned if ``p`` is a scalar.  Otherwise, ``np.array(p).size`` samples are "
"drawn."
msgstr ""

